Review of the business
Trading continued to be strong during the year to 31 March 2023 and turnover in both The Falstaff and The Rye Lodge hotels. The George in Rye Hotel has recovered well in the year after it reopened in May 2022 following the fire in July 2019. George on Rye has seen a strong increase in other income following a large insurance claim being realised in the year to 31 March 2023.
Principal risks and uncertainties
The key risks affecting the business are as follows:
Interest rate increases affecting finance costs, the business and subsequent cash flow;
Wider economic trends that show continued lack of consumer and corporate confidence;
Weather - extreme weather conditions e.g. lack of good weather in peak summer periods;
Increased level of competitive hotel supply in markets in which we operate.
